Expand your opportunity by getting involved and attending events. • After Hours Mix & Mingle – 2nd Tuesday of the month (5:30pm – 7pm) • Chamber Luncheons – 3rd Thursday of the month (11:45am – 1pm) • Before Hours Networking Breakfast – Last Thursday of the month (8am – 9am) Dates and event locations are subject to change. Please check event dates and times at www.JensenChamber.com. Make great connections and share your input by joining a Chamber committee. For additional information contact Ron Rose, President CEO, (772) 334-3444. Ron@JensenChamber.com. Becoming eligible to be selected as an Ambassador is one of the first steps you can take to get more involved. Ambassadors are a team of knowledgeable Chamber members that share with new, current, and potential members the benefits of Chamber involvement. Ambassadors help fellow members engage in the Chamber programs and events, as well as aid Chamber staff at our various networking and ribbon cutting events. To be selected as an Ambassador certain criterion must be met. To apply contact the Chamber (772) 334-3444, info@JensenChamber.com . The Government Relations Council advocates matters related to local and state government. The Council’s overall objective is to continually improve the business climate through dialogue with elected officials to raise awareness and stay in front of issues that may impact our business community. Council members review and develop pro-business public policy positions, share relevant legislative updates with the membership, and monitor issues that may impact business. The Council meets every other month in conjunction with our “Coffee with the Commissioner” program series. The Education Committee works to achieve a cooperative interchange of goals, information and activities between businesses and schools. Committee initiatives include Welcome Back Teachers & Staff Appreciation Breakfast, The Entrepreneurship Foundation Scholarship Program, Celebrating Influential Teachers & Students of the Month, and supporting Junior Achievement. The annual fundraising, presented by The Entrepreneurship Foundation and supported by the Chamber, is the Art, Music & Benefit Auction. Funds raised support the art and music programs at Jensen Beach Elementary School, Felix A. Williams Elementary School, Stuart Middle School, Jensen Beach High School, and the Environmental Studies Center. The committee meets the last Tuesday of each month September, October, and January through April. Community Engagement Volunteers work to enhance the image and quality of life of Jensen Beach through beautification projects and community events that keep Jensen Beach top-of-mind. Volunteers assist with Chamber produced events such as Taste of Jensen, Jensen Beach Fine Art & Craft Show, St. Patrick’s Day Festivities & Parade, Jammin’ Jensen, and the Jack-O- Lantern Blazer Bowling Bash. The Fundraising Committee seeks donations and grants to help fund programs and projects related to educational initiatives and historical preservation. Our Chamber supported 501c3 nonprofits are: The Entrepreneurship Foundation, Inc. is a specialized business educational foundation that provides resources needed to support entrepreneurial development in the community. The Foundation fosters, encourages and promotes an entrepreneurial culture and acts as the unifying source of educational, government and private sector resources to benefit current and future entrepreneurs. Contact Foundation President: Ed Griffith (772) 334-1950 The History Museum of Jensen Beach, Inc. preserves the heritage of Jensen Beach for the benefit of present and future generations. Housed in the Jensen Beach Community Center in downtown Jensen Beach, the museum promotes the collection, preservation, and educational interpretation of its people, institutions, and culture. The museum also displays early artifacts, photos, and documents. Contact Museum President: Ann Kagdis (772) 334-3444 JOIN THE CHAMBER ONLINE! DOWNLOAD APPLICATION PDF!
